    "Fig 10 shows the variance of metrics that vary most with prevalence as indicated by results shown in Figs 1 2 3.",
    "Here, we start with a single threshold, that is 0.5, gradually add more thresholds until all possible thresholds are added.",
    "We take the average of model evaluation metric values each time additional thresholds are added into the calculation.",
    "The thresholds are added incrementally based on their distance from 0.5.",
    "Those closest to 0.5 are added first, thus we gradually increase the span of thresholds used."
